The '1967â68 FA Cup' was the 87th season of the world's oldest football cup
competition, the Football Association Challenge Cup, commonly known as the FA
Cup. West Bromwich Albion won the competition, beating Everton 1â0 after extra
time in the final at Wembley, London.

Matches were played at the stadium of the team named first on the date specified
for each round, which was always a Saturday. If the weather was inclement, a
match may have been played at a different date to that originally planned. If
scores were level after 90 minutes had been played, a replay would take place at
the stadium of the second-named team later the same week. If the replayed match
was drawn further replays would be held at neutral venues until a winner was
determined. If scores were level after 90 minutes had been played in a replay, a
30-minute period of extra time would be played.
